opment, creating scalable APIs, and developing robust web systems using Python and Django. Strong experience in Python, SQL, and database management, with an emphasis on clean, efficient, and high-performance coding.", "image": "media/profile/Myself.jpeg", "college_name": "Mount Everest Secondary School", "college_location": "+2", "school_name": "Mount Everest Secondary School", "school_location": "SEE"}}, {"model": "main.skill", "pk": 1, "fields": {"name": "Python", "skill_img": "skills/python_logo-png.png"}}, {"model": "main.skill", "pk": 2, "fields": {"name": "Hypertext Markup Language(HTML)", "skill_img": "skills/Pngtreehtml_file_document_icon_4175819.png"}}, {"model": "main.skill", "pk": 3, "fields": {"name": "Django", "skill_img": "skills/django-logo-negative.png"}}, {"model": "main.skill", "pk": 4, "fields": {"name": "Cascading style sheet (css)", "skill_img": "skills/rendering-file-css-coding-png.png"}}, {"model": "main.project", "pk": 1, "fields": {"name": "Todo Application", "image": "projects/Todo_app.png", "project_details": "The Todo Application is a web-based task management system designed to help users organize their daily activities in a simple and efficient way. The application allows users to create, update, and manage tasks through an intuitive and user-friendly interface. It is built using Django for the backend and Bootstrap for the frontend, ensuring both functionality and responsiveness.\r\n\r\nUsers can easily add new tasks using a form, edit existing tasks whenever needed, and delete tasks that are no longer relevant. One of the key features of this application is the ability to mark tasks as completed, which helps users track their progress and stay productive. Completed tasks are visually distinguished from pending ones, making task management clearer and more organized.\r\n\r\nThe application uses Django’s ORM for handling database operations efficiently, while SQLite is used as the database for simplicity. Bootstrap is used to create a clean and responsive design that works well across different devices.\r\n\r\nOverall, this project demonstrates fundamental full-stack development skills, including CRUD operations, database management, and responsive UI design. It serves as a practical example of building a real-world application using Django.", "github_repo": "https://github.com/NischalParajuli/Django.git"}}, {"model": "main.project", "pk": 2, "fields": {"name": "Tweetz (Twitter Clone)", "image": "projects/Tweetz.png", "project_details": "Twwetz is a Django-based social media web application inspired by Twitter, designed to allow users to share short posts and interact with a dynamic content feed. The application focuses on providing a smooth and intuitive user experience while implementing core social media features such as tweet creation, editing, and deletion.\r\n\r\nUsers can register and log in securely using Django’s authentication system. Once logged in, they can create tweets with a character limit, edit or delete their own tweets, and optionally attach images to enhance their posts. The application ensures proper access control, allowing users to modify only their own content.\r\n\r\nA central feature of the application is the tweet feed, where all users’ posts are displayed in reverse chronological order, ensuring that the latest content appears first. Each user also has a dedicated profile page where they can view all their tweets and manage their personal information.\r\n\r\nThe backend is powered by Django and its ORM for efficient data handling, while SQLite is used for database management. Bootstrap is used to create a responsive and clean user interface.\r\n\r\nThis project showcases key concepts of full-stack web development, including authentication, CRUD operations, media handling, and structured application design.", "github_repo": "https://github.com/NischalParajuli/TweetZ.git"}}, {"model": "main.resume", "pk": 1, "fields": {"name": "Resume", "file": "resumes/Resume.pdf", "upl